==Hindi==
===Etymology===
From the Sanskrit
===Adjective===
'''पण्डित''' (paṇḍit or pandit)
#learned, wise, shrewd, clever, skillful in, conversant with

===Noun===
'''पण्डित''' (paṇḍit or pandit) {{m}}

#a scholar , a learned man , teacher , philosopher , a [[pandit]]

===Alternative spelling ===
*[[पंडित]]

