==Sanskrit==
===Adjective===
'''पण्डित''' (paṇḍit or pandit)
#learned, wise, shrewd, clever, skillful in, conversant with

===Noun===
'''पण्डित''' (paṇḍit or pandit) {{m}}

#a scholar , a learned man , teacher , philosopher , a [[pandit]]
#a Hindu Brahmin who has memorized a substantial portion of the Vedas, along with the corresponding rhythms and melodies for chanting or singing them.

